span>&gt;</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-name\">div</span>&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-name\">form</span>&gt;</span></span>\n</pre>\n</div>\n<h3 class=\"section-head\" id=\"h-width\"><a href=\"#h-width\">Width</a></h3>\n<p>Following framework-wide rules, it is very easy to manipulate form fields sizes. Just use <code>w50</code> class to make a field 50% wide or <code>w25</code> to a 25% wide.</p>\n<div class=\"example\">\n  <form action=\"\" class=\"form\" method=\"post\">\n    <input name=\"authorize-token\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"c6851d805bd96d2c91d52574c65d3ae26ce4b6bca43f560518a0bea61335f9d52acc6055807bf8616ff3d13d3882d5aa2f4b15a046562c1e6a9d932e369e9fad\">\n    <div class=\"form-item\">\n      <input class=\"w25\" type=\"text\" value=\".w25\">\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"form-item\">\n      <input class=\"w50\" type=\"text\" value=\".w50\">\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"form-item\">\n      <input class=\"w75\" type=\"text\" value=\".w75\">\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"form-item\">\n      <input type=\"text\" value=\"100% by default\">\n    </div>\n  </form>\n  <pre class=\"code skip\">&lt;form method=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"post\"</span> action=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"\"</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"form\"</span>&gt;\n    &lt;div <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"form-item\"</span>&gt;\n        &lt;input <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">type</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"text\"</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"w25\"</span>&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;div <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"form-item\"</span>&gt;\n        &lt;input <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">type</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"text\"</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"w50\"</span>&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;div <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"form-item\"</span>&gt;\n        &lt;input <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">type</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"text\"</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"w75\"</span>&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;div <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"form-item\"</span>&gt;\n        &lt;input <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">type</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"text\"</span> value=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"100% by default\"</span>&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n</pre>\n</div>\n<h3 class=\"section-head\" id=\"h-states\"><a href=\"#h-states\">States</a></h3>\n<p>By default, Kube features two different states: success and failure.</p>\n<div class=\"example\">\n  <form action=\"\" class=\"form\" method=\"post\">\n    <input name=\"authorize-token\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"c6851d805bd96d2c91d52574c65d3ae26ce4b6bca43f560518a0bea61335f9d52acc6055807bf8616ff3d13d3882d5aa2f4b15a046562c1e6a9d932e369e9fad\">\n    <div class=\"form-item\">\n      <label>Your height <span class=\"success\">Looks like a valid value</span></label> <input class=\"success\" type=\"text\">\n    </div>\n  </form>\n  <pre class=\"code skip\">&lt;form method=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"post\"</span> action=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"\"</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span></span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"form\"</span>&gt;\n    <span class=\"xml\"><span class=\"hljs-tag\">&lt;<span class